 extraordinary cultural capital of seers. The first cultural history of the seer, The Seer and the City illuminates the contests between religious and political powers in archaic and classical Greece.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHero (Greek mythology) 0aHero (Greek mythology). 0aOracles, Greek. 0aProphetszGreece. 0aReligion and politicszGreecexHistory. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Greece.2bisacsh  aancient greece.  aancient greek politics.  aancient world.  aantiquity.  aarchaic greece.  aarchaic.  aclassical greece.  aclassical world.  aclassical.  acolonial discourse.  acolonial.  acolonialism.  aculture.  adelphi.  adivination.  agreek culture.  agreek politics.  ahellenistic period.  aideological.  aideology.  aliterary analysis.  aliterary texts.  aoracle.  apolitics.  areligion.  areligious studies.  aseercraft.  aseers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052029500140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967915423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520967915/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles